=== EXAMPLE: scdoc_Classes_UGen_ex18 ===

DESCRIPTION: A very_dark pure_tone sound, with fm_or_inharmonic oscillator character around 441 Hz, featuring punchy attack and sustained envelope, with chaotic spectral movement, filtered with steep_rolloff character, and spectrally simple.

CATEGORIES:
  attack_time: punchy
  brightness: very_dark
  crest_factor_db: sustained
  envelope_flatness: flat
  harmonic_to_noise_ratio: pure_tone
  spectral_complexity_mean: simple
  spectral_flux_normalized: chaotic
  spectral_slope: steep_rolloff
  temporal_centroid: balanced

SYNTHESIS CONCEPTS (key values):
[oscillator]
  fundamental_freq: 441.2715
  harmonic_decay_rate: -13.8327
  harmonic_regularity: 0.5864
  pitch_clarity: 47.7178
  inharmonicity: 0.3431
  type: fm_or_inharmonic
[filter]
  spectral_slope: -5.7796
  resonance_freq: 0.0000

SUPERCOLLIDER CODE:
// Title: UGen Example 18
// Author: SC Documentation
// URL: http://doc.sccode.org/Classes/UGen.html
// Tags: UGen, Classes
// ---
// --- Example 18 ---
// note different syntax in these two examples
{ if(LFNoise1.kr(1.0, 0.5, 0.5), SinOsc.ar, Saw.ar) * 0.1 }.play;

{ Trig1.ar(Dust.ar(3), 0.2).lag(0.1).if(FSinOsc.ar(440), FSinOsc.ar(880)) * 0.1 }.play;
